AND WE ARE HERE TODAY TO HONOR HOW ONE PERSON,
OUR HONOREE, RUTH BADER GINSBURG, KNOCKED

00:11:43.150 --> 00:11:49.750
ON CLOSED DOORS, OPENED THEM, AND THEN HELD
THEM OPEN FOR OTHERS.

00:11:49.750 --> 00:11:55.040
WHEN JUSTICE GINSBURG GRADUATED FROM COLUMBIA
LAW SCHOOL, IT SEEMED UNLIKELY SHE WOULD GET

00:11:55.040 --> 00:11:57.330
A CLERKSHIP, DESPITE HER CLASS RANK.

00:11:57.330 --> 00:12:00.480
IF YOU WERE HERE THIS MORNING, YOU HEARD MICHAEL
KLARMAN TELL THIS STORY.

00:12:00.480 --> 00:12:03.320
BUT I'M GOING TO TELL IT AGAIN BECAUSE IT'S
SUCH A GOOD ONE.

00:12:03.320 --> 00:12:10.561
IT WASN'T JUST THAT SHE WAS A WOMAN, BUT SHE
WAS ALSO A MOTHER. WHO WOULD HIRE HER? PROFESSOR

00:12:10.561 --> 00:12:16.880
GERRY GUNTHER, THEN ON THE COLUMBIA FACULTY,
RECOMMENDED JUSTIVE GINSBURG TO MANY, MANY

00:12:16.880 --> 00:12:23.430
JUDGES. HE EVEN PROMISED THESE PERSPECTIVE
EMPLOYERS, THAT IF SHE DIDN'T WORK OUT HE

00:12:23.430 --> 00:12:26.970
WOULD FIND A MALE LAWYER TO REPLACE HER.

00:12:26.970 --> 00:12:33.240
WITH THAT PROMISE, JUSTICE GINSBURG WAS FINALLY
HIRED BY JUDGE EDMOND PALMIERI OF THE SOUTHERN

00:12:33.240 --> 00:12:34.440
DISTRICT.

00:12:34.440 --> 00:12:36.300
AND HOW DID IT GO?

00:12:36.300 --> 00:12:44.790
SO SUCCESSFULLY THAT THE NEXT CLERK HIRED
BY JUDGE PALMIERI WAS A WOMAN. JUSTICE GINSBURG

00:12:44.790 --> 00:12:47.940
THEN OPENED OTHER DOORS IN OTHER WAYS.

00:12:47.940 --> 00:12:54.010
AS THE COFOUNDER OF THE WOMEN'S RIGHT PROJECT
OF THE ACLU, SHE CHALLENGED INEQUALITY BY

00:12:54.010 --> 00:13:02.060
CHANGING LAWS PIECE BY PIECE, CASE BY CASE,
WORKING WITH AND FOR EVERYDAY PEOPLE TO ADDRESS

00:13:02.060 --> 00:13:04.320
EVERYDAY INJUSTICES.

00:13:04.320 --> 00:13:08.560
SHE WON FIVE OF THE SIX CASES SHE BROUGHT
TO THE SUPREME COURT.

00:13:08.560 --> 00:13:14.900
HER VICTORIES LED TO IMPORTANT IMPROVEMENTS
IN THE LIVES OF WOMEN AND MEN AND THEIR FAMILIES.

00:13:14.900 --> 00:13:21.340
SUCH AS SECURING SOCIAL SECURITY BENEFITS
FOR FATHERS, OBTAINING SPOUSAL BENEFITS FOR

00:13:21.340 --> 00:13:28.850
WOMEN IN THE MILITARY, AND ELIMINATING GENDER
BASED JURY SERVICE EXEMPTIONS IN PART BY ARGUING

00:13:28.850 --> 00:13:35.610
THAT OPTIONAL JURY DUTY FOR WOMEN TREATS WOMEN'S
SERVICE ON JURIES AS LESS VALUABLE THAN MEN'S

00:13:35.610 --> 00:13:40.380
AND THREATENS WOMEN'S RIGHT TO TRIAL BY A
JURY OF THEIR PEERS.

00:13:40.380 --> 00:13:46.850
BEGINNING IN 1980, RUTH BADER GINSBURG SERVED
ON THE U.S. COURT OF APPEALS FOR THE DISTRICT

00:13:46.850 --> 00:13:47.850
COLUMBIA.

00:13:47.850 --> 00:13:54.750
SOME FEARED THAT SHE, A PASSIONATE ADVOCATE
FOR THE COURTS WOULD INTENSIFY A INTENSIFY

00:13:54.750 --> 00:14:01.920
WHAT WAS ALREADY CONSIDERED A HIGHLY POLARIZED
COURT. AGAIN SHE DEIFED EXPECTATIONS.

00:14:01.920 --> 00:14:04.960
SHE WAS PARTIAL TO IMPARTIALITY.

00:14:04.960 --> 00:14:10.750
SHE SOUGHT CLARITY AND CONSISTENCY IN THE
IMPORTANT WORK OF THE APPEALS COURT.

00:14:10.750 --> 00:14:18.150
AS A JUDGE, SHE DEMONSTRATED A COMMITMENT
NOT TO GENERATING HEAT, BUT TO SHEDDING LIGHT.

00:14:18.150 --> 00:14:24.550
WHEN PRESIDENT CLINTON APPOINTED RUTH BADER
GINSBURG TO THE SUPREME COURT IN 1993, SHE

00:14:24.550 --> 00:14:30.420
JOINED SANDRA DAY O'CONNOR AS ONLY THE SECOND
WOMAN ON THE COURT IN ITS HISTORY.

00:14:30.420 --> 00:14:37.339
IT WAS AN INSTITUTION SO MALE THAT A POPULAR
HISTORY OF THE COURT WAS ENTITLED THE BRETHREN.

00:14:37.339 --> 00:14:43.350
THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF WOMEN JUDGES,
AN ORGANIZATION WHOSE PAPERS WE'RE GRATEFUL

00:14:43.350 --> 00:14:48.420
TO HAVE IN THE RADCLIFFE SCHLESINGER LIBRARY,
AND WHOSE MEMBERSHIP IS VERY WELL REPRESENTED

00:14:48.420 --> 00:14:55.290
HERE TODAY, BRILLIANTLY UNDERSCORED THE POINT
BY GIVING JUSTICE O'CONNOR A T SHIRT THAT

00:14:55.290 --> 00:15:04.150
SAID I'M SANDRA, NOT RUTH. AND JUSTICE GINSBURG
GETS MADE, I'M RUTH NOT SANDRA.

00:15:04.150 --> 00:15:06.610
JUSTICE GINSBURG WAS HARDLY INTIMIDATED.

00:15:06.610 --> 00:15:14.670
IF SHE WAS, NO ONE WHO OBSERVED HER ASKING
QUESTIONS FROM THE BENCH, ENGAGING COLLEAGUES

00:15:14.670 --> 00:15:18.300
OR ISSUING QUESTIONS COULD DETECT IT.

00:15:18.300 --> 00:15:22.950
A SELECTION OF MAJORITY OPINIONS SHE WROTE
INCLUDES ELIMINATING THE BAN ON WOMEN AT THE

00:15:22.950 --> 00:15:29.330
VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE. ENABLING A PARENT
TO TRY TO REGAIN CUSTODY OF HER CHILDREN DESPITE

00:15:29.330 --> 00:15:32.990
HER INABILITY TO PAY COURT FEES.

00:15:32.990 --> 00:15:38.360
STRENGTHENING THE POWER OF THE FEDERAL EPA
TO ENFORCE THE CLEAN AIR ACT.

00:15:38.360 --> 00:15:42.850
DEFENDING THE RIGHTS OF PEOPLE WITH MENTAL
DISABILITIES TO LIVE IN COMMUNITY SETTINGS

00:15:42.850 --> 00:15:46.120
AND NOT BE INSTITUTIONALIZED.

00:15:46.120 --> 00:15:51.490
UPHOLDING THE RIGHT OF A DEATH PENALTY DEFENDANT
TO TURN TO THE UNITED STATES SUPREME COURT

00:15:51.490 --> 00:15:58.670
AS A COURT OF LAST RESORT, AND SHIELDING CITIZENS
FROM UNREASONABLE SEARCH AND SEIZURE.

00:15:58.670 --> 00:16:04.100
A DOZEN YEARS AGO JUSTICE GINSBURG WAS PART
OF THE MAJORITY OPINION ALLOWING RACE TO BE

00:16:04.100 --> 00:16:09.170
A PART OF FACTOR IN LAW SCHOOL ADMISSIONS
IN RECOGNITION THAT DISCRIMINATION LIVES ON

00:16:09.170 --> 00:16:13.230
IN AMERICA DESPITE OUR HOPES AND IDEALS TO
THE CONTARY.

00:16:13.230 --> 00:16:20.910
WHILE SOME IN THE MAJORITY FORECAST THAT RACE
BASED CONSIDERATIONS WOULD SURELY NOT BE RELEVANT

00:16:20.910 --> 00:16:28.560
25 YEARS AFTER THE DECISION, JUSTICES GINSBURG
AND BREYER TOOK A LESS SANGUINED VIEW.

00:16:28.560 --> 00:16:31.810
THESE DAYS THEIR DOUBTS SEEM ALL TOO PRESCIENT.

00:16:31.810 --> 00:16:38.760
EVEN WHEN JUSTICE GINSBURG WAS NOT IN THE
MAJORITY, SHE SHAPES THE WAY WE LIVE AND WORK.

00:16:38.760 --> 00:16:45.010
FOR EXAMPLE, IN THE LILLY LEDBETTER EQUAL
PAY CASE, THE MAJORITY DECISION AND PRACTICE

00:16:45.010 --> 00:16:49.420
ALLOWED PAY DISCRIMINATION TO CONTINUE INDEFINITELY.

00:16:49.420 --> 00:16:55.380
WHEN JUSTICE GINSBURG DELIVERED HER DISSENT,
SHE CHARGED CONGRESS WITH CORRECTING HER COLLEAGUE'S

00:16:55.380 --> 00:16:57.470
INTERPRETATION OF THE LAW.

00:16:57.470 --> 00:17:04.020
WITHIN 18 MONTHS, WHICH IS RECORD SPEED IN
OUR SYSTEM OF GOVERNMENT, CONGRESS PASSED

00:17:04.020 --> 00:17:11.040
THE LLILY LEDBETTER FAIR PAY ACT, AND IT WAS
SIGNED INTO LAW BY PRESIDENT OBAMA.

