THE ONE WHO WRITES PERHAPS THE MOST OF THE
CIVIL PROCEDURE CASES.

00:36:56.890 --> 00:37:03.479
AND WHO FORGED A CAREER AS A BRILLIANT LITIGATOR
FOR THE WOMEN'S RIGHTS PROJECT OF THE ACLU

00:37:03.479 --> 00:37:08.440
BACK IN THE EARLY '70S. AND AT A TIME WHEN
THERE WAS NO EQUAL RIGHTS AMENDMENT,

00:37:08.440 --> 00:37:14.569
NO UPDATE TO THE WORDS OF THE CONSTITUTION
IN THE 14TH AMENDMENT IN 1868 THAT SAID NO

00:37:14.569 --> 00:37:18.299
STATE SHOULD DEPRIVE ANY PERSON OF EQUAL PROTECTION
OF THE LAWS.

00:37:18.299 --> 00:37:24.219
BUT NO CLEAR EXTENSION OF THAT PRINCIPLE,
TO THE PRINCIPLE OF SEX EQUALITY.

00:37:24.219 --> 00:37:29.309
JUSTICE GINSBURG MORE THAN ANYONE ELSE FORGED
THAT DEVELOPMENT IN THE LAW.

00:37:29.309 --> 00:37:33.930
JUSTICE GINSBURG, I WONDER IF WE COULD START
BY GOING BACK TO THE '70S, AND HAVE YOU TALK

00:37:33.930 --> 00:37:40.049
ABOUT THE TURNING POINT CASES, THE CASE OF
REED V. REED. THAT YOU WORKED ON, OR FRONTIERO

00:37:40.049 --> 00:37:41.049
V. RICHARDSON.

00:37:41.049 --> 00:37:43.839
CAN YOU TAKE US BACK AND TELL US ABOUT THOSE
CASES?

00:37:43.839 --> 00:37:52.829
&gt;&gt; RUTH BADER GINSBURG: KATHLEEN, BEFORE I
DO THAT LET ME SAY THAT I DON'T THINK THERE'S

00:37:52.829 --> 00:37:59.519
BEEN A HIGHER NOTE THAN THERE WAS THIS MORNING
AND WITH MY DEAR COLLEAGUE JUSTICE SOUTER.

00:37:59.519 --> 00:38:03.039
I LOVED IT ALL AND I HOPE YOU ENJOYED IT.

00:38:03.039 --> 00:38:07.559
AND I WOULD LIKE TO ADD A P.S. TO SOMETHING
MY COLLEAGUE SAID.

00:38:07.559 --> 00:38:15.529
IN THE YEARS WE SERVED TOGETHER, JUSTICE SOUTER
AND I VOTED ALIKE MORE THAN ANY TWO OTHER

00:38:15.529 --> 00:38:20.180
JUSTICES, EVEN MORE THAN JUSTICE SCALIA AND
JUSTICE THOMAS.

00:38:20.180 --> 00:38:30.849
I MISS HIM, BUT I OCCUPY THE CHAMBERS THAT
WERE HIS WHEN HE WAS ON THE COURT.

00:38:30.849 --> 00:38:34.700
THEY LOOK A LITTLE DIFFERENT.

00:38:34.700 --> 00:38:44.569
BUT I THINK OF HIM WITH GREAT APPRECIATION
FOR WHAT A WONDERFUL COLLEAGUE HE WAS.

00:38:44.569 --> 00:38:47.239
ANYWAY, SALLY REED.

00:38:47.239 --> 00:38:58.710
SALLY REED IS A WOMAN FROM BOISE, IDAHO AND
SHE HAS HAD A TRAGIC OCCURRENCE IN HER LIFE.

00:38:58.710 --> 00:39:07.619
SALLY WAS CHILDLESS FOR YEARS AND THEN SHE
AND HER HUSBAND ADOPTED A BABY BOY AND THEN

00:39:07.619 --> 00:39:11.059
THEY HAD A FALLING OUT SO THEY SEPARATED.

00:39:11.059 --> 00:39:20.460
AND THE YOUNG BOY WAS GIVEN TO SALLY AS PRIMARY
CUSTODIAN BECAUSE THE CHILD WAS WHAT THE LAW

00:39:20.460 --> 00:39:23.910
CALLED OF TENDER YEARS.

00:39:23.910 --> 00:39:30.470
WHEN THE BOY REACHED HIS TEENS, FATHER APPLIED
FOR CUSTODY.

00:39:30.470 --> 00:39:34.490
HIS ARGUMENT WAS NOW THE BOY NEEDS TO BE PREPARED
FOR A MAN'S WORLD.

00:39:34.490 --> 00:39:37.519
THE JUDGE SAID YES.

00:39:37.519 --> 00:39:38.759
SALLY OPPOSED IT.

00:39:38.759 --> 00:39:44.049
SHE THOUGHT THE FATHER WOULD NOT BE A GOOD
INFLUENCE ON THE BOY.

00:39:44.049 --> 00:39:48.290
AND SADLY SHE PROVED TO BE RIGHT.

00:39:48.290 --> 00:39:56.059
ONE DAY THE BOY WAS SORELY DEPRESSED AND HE
TOOK OUT ONE OF HIS FATHER'S MANY GUNS AND

00:39:56.059 --> 00:39:59.299
HE COMMITTED SUICIDE.

00:39:59.299 --> 00:40:05.990
SO SALLY WANTED TO BE APPOINTED ADMINISTRATOR
OF HIS ESTATE.

00:40:05.990 --> 00:40:11.710
THE PROBATE COURT JUDGE TOLD HER I'M SORRY
SALLY, BUT THE LAW IS CLEAR.

00:40:11.710 --> 00:40:21.940
THE IDAHO PROBATE CODE SAYS AS BETWEEN PEOPLE
EQUALLY ENTITLED TO ADMINISTER'S A DESCENDANTS

00:40:21.940 --> 00:40:28.880
ESTATE, MALES MUST BE PREFERRED TO FEMALES.

00:40:28.880 --> 00:40:38.509
IT WAS THE PERFECT STATUTE TO ATTACK AS DISCRIMINATING
ARBITRARILY AGAINST A WOMAN.

00:40:38.509 --> 00:40:45.680
BUT WHAT SALLY REID'S CASE BROUGHT HOME TO
ME WAS THAT THIS IS A WOMAN WHO WAS HARDLY

00:40:45.680 --> 00:40:47.380
SOPHISTICATED.

00:40:47.380 --> 00:40:49.549
SHE PROBABLY DIDN'T CALL HERSELF A FEMINIST.

00:40:49.549 --> 00:40:53.279
SHE PROBABLY DIDN'T EVEN KNOW WHAT THE WORD
MEANT.

00:40:53.279 --> 00:41:00.430
BUT SHE THOUGHT SHE SUFFERED AN INJUSTICE
AND THAT THE LEGAL SYSTEM COULD MAKE IT RIGHT.

00:41:00.430 --> 00:41:05.480
I DON'T KNOW HOW MANY COUNTRIES THAT WOULD
BE SO.

00:41:05.480 --> 00:41:10.880
SO SALLY WENT THROUGH THREE LEVELS OF THE
IDAHO COURTS.

00:41:10.880 --> 00:41:15.989
SHE LOST THE FIRST TIME, WON THE SECOND TIME,
AND LOST THE THIRD TIME.

00:41:15.989 --> 00:41:23.010
THE SUPREME COURT HEARD HER CASE AND FOR THE
FIRST TIME IN THE HISTORY OF THAT COURT THEY

00:41:23.010 --> 00:41:32.930
SAID THAT A GENDER CLASSIFICATION VIOLATED
THE PRINCIPLE OF THE EQUAL PROTECTION OF THE

00:41:32.930 --> 00:41:33.930
LAWS.

00:41:33.930 --> 00:41:37.789
&gt;&gt; KATHLEEN SULLIVAN: AND THAT WAS QUITE REMARKABLE,
BECAUSE THE EQUAL RIGHTS AMENDMENT, WHICH

00:41:37.789 --> 00:41:43.559
HAD BEEN ENACTED IN CONGRESS NUMEROUS TIMES,
BUT NEVER RATIFIED BY THE STATES WAS NOT YET

00:41:43.559 --> 00:41:44.559
ENFORCED.

00:41:44.559 --> 00:41:48.710
SO YOU HAD TO MAKE NEW LAW WITH THE EXISTING
LANGUAGE OF THE CONSTITUTION.

00:41:48.710 --> 00:41:49.940
HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

00:41:49.940 --> 00:41:54.319
HOW DID YOU CONVINCE THEM THAT THE LAW IN
IDAHO WAS IRRATIONAL TO DISCRIMINATE BETWEEN

00:41:54.319 --> 00:41:55.319
MEN AND WOMEN.

00:41:55.319 --> 00:42:00.259
&gt;&gt; RUTH BADER GINSBURG: WE WENT THROUGH EVERY
EQUAL PROTECTION DECISION, THERE WEREN'T THAT

00:42:00.259 --> 00:42:02.989
MANY OUTSIDE OF THE RACE AREA

00:42:02.989 --> 00:42:12.099
AND PICKED UP THE BEST LANGUAGE THAT WE COULD
FIND.

00:42:12.099 --> 00:42:18.869
AND IT WAS JUST THE LIFE STORY OF THIS WOMAN
AND THE ARBITRARINESS OF THE LAW.

00:42:18.869 --> 00:42:27.829
NOW THE LAW, IT WAS UNDERSTANDABLE BECAUSE
IT WAS COPIED BY IDAHO FROM CALIFORNIA.

00:42:27.829 --> 00:42:33.890
IT WAS MIDDLE 19TH CENTURY LAW.

00:42:33.890 --> 00:42:41.349
THE THINKING WAS THAT WOMEN ONCE THEY MARRIED
LOSE THEIR RIGHT TO CONTRACT IN THEIR OWN

00:42:41.349 --> 00:42:46.910
NAME, SUE AND BE SUED IN THEIR OWN NAMES,
HOLD PROPERTY.

00:42:46.910 --> 00:42:54.810
SO ALL THINGS CONSIDERED, IF YOU HAD A CHOICE
BETWEEN A MAN WHO WAS COMPETENT AND A WOMAN

00:42:54.810 --> 00:43:00.099
WHO WAS UNDER THESE LAW IMPOSED DISABILITIES,
YOU WOULD PREFER THE MAN.

00:43:00.099 --> 00:43:05.960
&gt;&gt; KATHLEEN SULLIVAN: NOW A NUMBER OF THE
LAWS THAT YOU CHALLENGED DURING THIS PIVOTAL

00:43:05.960 --> 00:43:14.260
PERIOD WITH THE ACLU WOMEN'S RIGHTS PROJECT
WERE ACTUALLY LAWS THAT GAVE A PARENT PRIVILEGES

00:43:14.260 --> 00:43:16.660
TO WOMEN OVER MEN.

00:43:16.660 --> 00:43:23.359
LAWS THAT ASSUMED THAT MILITARY WIVES WERE
DEPENDENT ON THEIR SERVICE MEMBER'S, HUSBAND'S

00:43:23.359 --> 00:43:24.359
INCOME.

00:43:24.359 --> 00:43:30.589
OR SOCIAL SECURITY CLASSIFICATIONS THAT ASSUMED
THAT WIVES WERE DEPENDENT ON HUSBANDS, BUT

00:43:30.589 --> 00:43:37.469
HUSBANDS WOULD HAVE TO PROVE DEPENDENCY TO
GET BENEFITS EARNED BY THEIR WIVES.

00:43:37.469 --> 00:43:43.039
YOU MIGHT SAY THEY WERE LAWS THAT WERE SEX
DISCRIMINATION, BUT NOMINALLY IN FAVOR OF

00:43:43.039 --> 00:43:44.039
WOMEN.

00:43:44.039 --> 00:43:45.829
AND YET YOU TOOK THOSE CASES ON, AS WELL.

00:43:45.829 --> 00:43:50.970
IN CASES LIKE FRONTIERO, AND LATER IN CASE
LIKE WIESENFELD.

00:43:50.970 --> 00:43:56.299
CAN YOU TELL US A LITTLE BIT ABOUT WHY YOU
CHALLENGED ON BEHALF OF MEN SOME OF THESE

00:43:56.299 --> 00:43:58.619
APPARENT PRIVILEGES FOR LADIES?

00:43:58.619 --> 00:44:05.269
&gt;&gt; RUTH BADER GINSBURG: THE OBJECT WAS TO
GET AT THE STEREOTYPE THAT HELD WOMEN BACK

00:44:05.269 --> 00:44:11.170
FROM DOING WHATEVER THEIR TALENT WOULD ALLOW
THEM TO DO.

00:44:11.170 --> 00:44:15.789
THE NOTION WAS THERE WERE SEPARATE SPHERES
FOR THE SEXES.

00:44:15.789 --> 00:44:21.450
MEN WERE THE DOERS IN THE WORLD OF COMMERCE.

00:44:21.450 --> 00:44:29.920
AND WOMEN WERE THE STAY AT HOME TYPES WHO
LOOKED AFTER THE HEARTH AND THE CHILDREN.

00:44:29.920 --> 00:44:36.339
AND WHAT WE WERE TRYING TO ACCOMPLISH WAS
TO GET RID OF ALL LAWS BASED ON THAT STEREOTYPE

00:44:36.339 --> 00:44:43.749
SO PEOPLE, WOMEN AS WELL AS MEN COULD BE IN
THE WORDS OF A SONG POPULAR IN THE EARLY '70s,

00:44:43.749 --> 00:44:45.730
FREE TO BE YOU AND ME.

00:44:45.730 --> 00:44:46.730
[LAUGHTER]

00:44:46.730 --> 00:44:56.509
STEPHEN WIESENFELD'S CASE WAS A TRAGIC CIRCUMSTANCE.

00:44:56.509 --> 00:44:59.809
HE WAS MARRIED TO A HIGH SCHOOL MATH TEACHER.

00:44:59.809 --> 00:45:05.660
THEIR DIVISION AT HOME HE WAS THE PRINCIPLE
HOME BODY, AND SHE WAS THE PRINCIPLE EARNER.

00:45:05.660 --> 00:45:11.039
SHE HAD A HEALTHY PREGNANCY, SHE WAS TEACHING
INTO HER 9TH MONTH.

00:45:11.039 --> 00:45:13.809
SHE WENT TO THE HOSPITAL TO GIVE BIRTH.

00:45:13.809 --> 00:45:21.450
THE DOCTOR CAME OUT AND TOLD STEPHEN YOU HAVE
A HEALTHY BABY BOY, BUT YOUR WIFE DIED OF

00:45:21.450 --> 00:45:22.450
AN EMBOLISM.

00:45:22.450 --> 00:45:30.180
SO STEPHEN VOWED THAT HE WOULD BE THE CARE
GIVING PARENT.

00:45:30.180 --> 00:45:34.660
HE WOULD NOT WORK FULL TIME UNTIL HIS CHILD
WAS IN SCHOOL FULL TIME.

00:45:34.660 --> 00:45:40.440
AND HE COULD MANAGE THAT, HE THOUGHT, BY WHAT
WERE CALLED CHILD AND CARE SOCIAL SECURITY

00:45:40.440 --> 00:45:41.440
BENEFITS.

00:45:41.440 --> 00:45:47.229
HE COULD EARN UP TO THE EARNINGS LIMIT, WHAT
HE EARNED, PLUS THE SOCIAL SECURITY.

00:45:47.229 --> 00:45:51.469
HE COULD MANAGE TO CARE FOR HIS CHILD AND
HIMSELF.

00:45:51.469 --> 00:45:58.940
SO HE WENT TO THE SOCIAL SECURITY OFFICE TO
ASK FOR THESE CHILD IN CARE BENEFITS AND WAS

00:45:58.940 --> 00:46:06.029
TOLD THIS IS A STATUTE, YOU SEE, IT SAYS MOTHER'S
BENEFITS.

00:46:06.029 --> 00:46:08.489
THEY WEREN'T AVAILABLE TO THE FATHER.

00:46:08.489 --> 00:46:16.400
AND HOW THE CASE BEGAN, STEPHEN WROTE A LETTER
TO THE EDITOR OF HIS LOCAL NEWSPAPER IN EDISON,

00:46:16.400 --> 00:46:18.670
NEW JERSEY.

00:46:18.670 --> 00:46:24.410
THE LETTER SAID I HAVE BEEN HEARING A LOT
ABOUT WOMEN'S LIB.

00:46:24.410 --> 00:46:26.579
LET ME TELL YOU MY STORY.

00:46:26.579 --> 00:46:34.650
THE TAGLINE AFTER HE SAID I DON'T GET THESE
BENEFITS AS A PARENT.

00:46:34.650 --> 00:46:37.410
IT MAKES NO SENSE.

00:46:37.410 --> 00:46:41.009
DOES GLORIA STEINEM KNOW ABOUT THIS?

00:46:41.009 --> 00:46:42.019
[LAUGHTER]

00:46:42.019 --> 00:46:50.210
WELL SOMEONE WHO WAS ON THE SPANISH FACULTY
AT RUTGERS UNIVERSITY, AND A FRIEND, CALLED

00:46:50.210 --> 00:46:55.989
ME AND SAID THIS ISN'T RIGHT, IS IT?

00:46:55.989 --> 00:47:02.839
SO I SUGGESTED THAT STEPHEN WIESENFELD CALL
THE NEW JERSEY AFFILIATE OF THE ACLU.

00:47:02.839 --> 00:47:08.000
AND WE TOOK THAT CASE FROM THE DISTRICT COURT
TO THE SUPREME COURT.

00:47:08.000 --> 00:47:13.710
I'M VERY PROUD OF THIS BECAUSE WE GOT THE
DECISION FROM THE SUPREME COURT BEFORE JASON,

00:47:13.710 --> 00:47:14.710
THE BABY, TURNED THREE.

00:47:14.710 --> 00:47:19.750
AND THAT'S A RECORD, REALLY A RECORD!

00:47:19.750 --> 00:47:21.089
[APPLAUSE]

00:47:21.089 --> 00:47:33.450
ANYWAY, IT WAS A UNANIMOUS JUDGMENT, BUT THEY
DIVIDED THREE WAYS ON WHO WAS THE VICTIM OF

00:47:33.450 --> 00:47:35.160
THE DISCRIMINATION.

00:47:35.160 --> 00:47:38.199
THE MAJORITY SAID OF COURSE IT'S THE WAGE
EARNING WOMAN.

00:47:38.199 --> 00:47:44.699
SHE PAYS THE SAME SOCIAL SECURITY TAXES AS
A MAN PAYS, BUT THE GOVERNMENT DOESN'T GIVE

00:47:44.699 --> 00:47:50.229
HER FAMILY THE SAME PROTECTION IT WOULD GIVE
TO A MAN'S FAMILY.

00:47:50.229 --> 00:47:56.420
AND THEN IT WAS DISCRIMINATION A COUPLE OF
THEM THOUGHT AGAINST THE MALE AS PARENT BECAUSE

00:47:56.420 --> 00:48:05.630
HE WOULDN'T HAVE THE OPPORTUNITY TO BE THE
PERSONAL, PRIMARY CAREGIVER OF HIS CHILD.

00:48:05.630 --> 00:48:13.839
AND THEN THERE WAS ONE WHO LATER BECAME MY
CHIEF WHO SAID IT'S TOTALLY ARBITRARY FROM

00:48:13.839 --> 00:48:15.849
THE POINT OF VIEW OF THE BABY.

00:48:15.849 --> 00:48:24.209
WHY SHOULD THE BABY HAVE THE OPPORTUNITY FOR
THE CARE OF A SOUL SURVIVING PARENT ONLY WHEN

00:48:24.209 --> 00:48:27.799
THAT PARENT IS FEMALE, NOT MALE?

00:48:27.799 --> 00:48:34.209
PEOPLE WERE ASTONISHED BECAUSE IT WAS THE
FIRST TIME THAT THEN JUSTICE REHNQUIST HAD

00:48:34.209 --> 00:48:39.000
EVER FOUND A LAW OFFENSIVE TO THE EQUAL PROTECTION
PRINCIPLE.

00:48:39.000 --> 00:48:40.000
[LAUGHTER]

00:48:40.000 --> 00:48:46.029
&gt;&gt; KATHLEEN SULLIVAN: SO THAT WAS A REMARKABLE
DECISION TO HAVE IT COME DOWN UNANIMOUSLY.

00:48:46.029 --> 00:48:51.900
AND IT WAS A WAY OF SAYING THAT A LAW THAT
SEEMS TO GIVE WOMEN SPECIAL PRIVILEGES AND

00:48:51.900 --> 00:48:57.849
PROTECTION CAN ACTUALLY BE DISCRIMINATORY
AGAINST WOMEN WAGE EARNERS AND SERVICE MEMBERS,

00:48:57.849 --> 00:49:02.969
AND DISCRIMINATORY AGAINST MEN WHO ARE PLAYING
THE ROLE OF PARENT OR CARETAKER OF THE CHILDREN

00:49:02.969 --> 00:49:09.249
AFTER A SPOUSE HAS DIED, AND IT CREATES THESE
STEREOTYPES, AND THAT'S NO DOUBT WHAT LED

00:49:09.249 --> 00:49:16.329
JUSTICE BRENNAN, AND THE CONCURRENCE IN THE
FRONTIERO CASE THAT YOU WON SPECTACULARLY,

00:49:16.329 --> 00:49:22.559
WHAT LOOKS LIKE BEING PUT ON A PEDESTAL MAY
SOMETIMES BE A CAGE IMPRISONING WOMEN IN OLD

00:49:22.559 --> 00:49:23.749
STEREOTYPES.

00:49:23.749 --> 00:49:31.670
SO BETWEEN REED AND FRONTIERO AND WIESENFELD
YOU REALLY LAID THE GROUNDWORK FOR THE LAW

00:49:31.670 --> 00:49:37.849
THAT STARTED TO BREAK DOWN THOSE ARCHAIC STEREOTYPES.

00:49:37.849 --> 00:49:41.150
I'D LIKE TO ASK YOU IF YOU WOULD TALK ABOUT
THIS.

00:49:41.150 --> 00:49:47.679
WHAT WAS THE ROLE OF POPULAR OPINION OR THE
EVOLVING SOCIAL CONSENSUS IN THOSE DECISIONS?

00:49:47.679 --> 00:49:50.719
&gt;&gt; RUTH BADER GINSBURG: IT MADE ALL THE DIFFERENCE.

00:49:50.719 --> 00:49:58.959
THE LITIGATION IN THE '70s WOULD HAVE BEEN
IMPOSSIBLE IN THE '60s. LET ME GIVE YOU AN

00:49:58.959 --> 00:50:00.410
EXAMPLE.

00:50:00.410 --> 00:50:02.819
JURY DUTY WAS MENTIONED THIS MORNING.

00:50:02.819 --> 00:50:09.150
THERE WAS A CASE IN 1961, THESE WERE THE YEARS
OF THE QUOTE LIBERAL WARREN COURT.

00:50:09.150 --> 00:50:14.569
THE CASE INVOLVED GWENDOLYN HOYT.

00:50:14.569 --> 00:50:18.930
TODAY WE WOULD CALL HER A BATTERED WOMEN.

00:50:18.930 --> 00:50:27.279
SHE ONE DAY HAD BEEN HUMILIATED TO THE BREAKING
POINT BY HER PHILANDERING, ABUSIVE HUSBAND.

00:50:27.279 --> 00:50:35.440
SHE TURNED TO THE CORNER OF THE ROOM AND THERE
WAS HER YOUNG SON'S BASEBALL BAT.

00:50:35.440 --> 00:50:42.400
AND SHE TOOK IT AND HIT HER SOUSE OVER THE
HEAD AND HE FELL AGAINST THE STONE FLOOR,

00:50:42.400 --> 00:50:49.460
END OF THEIR ALTERCATION, AND THE BEGINNING
OF THE MURDER PROSECUTION.

00:50:49.460 --> 00:50:58.950
THIS OCCURED IN HILLSBORO COUNTY FLORIDA,
AND AT THOSE DAYS WOMEN WERE NOT ON JURY ROLLS.

00:50:58.950 --> 00:51:05.599
THEY COULD COME TO THE CLERKS OFFICE AND SIGN
UP, BUT OTHERWISE THEY WEREN'T THERE.

00:51:05.599 --> 00:51:12.900
SHE WAS TRIED BEFORE AN ALL MALE JURY, AND
SHE HAD THE NOTION NOT THAT NECESSARILY SHE

00:51:12.900 --> 00:51:16.199
WOULD BE ACQUITTED IF WOMEN WERE ON THE JURY.

00:51:16.199 --> 00:51:23.519
BUT THE CHOICE BETWEEN MURDER AND MANSLAUGHTER,
THE WOMEN ON THE JURY MAY HAVE SWUNG IT TO

00:51:23.519 --> 00:51:26.569
THE LESSER CRIME OF MANSLAUGHTER.

00:51:26.569 --> 00:51:31.140
SHE WAS CONVICTED OF MURDER BY AN ALL MALE
JURY.

00:51:31.140 --> 00:51:37.430
WHEN HER CASE GOT TO THE SUPREME COURT IN
1961, THE VIEW WAS, WE DON'T UNDERSTAND THIS

00:51:37.430 --> 00:51:38.430
COMPLAINT.

00:51:38.430 --> 00:51:43.630
WOMEN HAVE THE BEST OF BOTH WORLDS, THEY CAN
SIGN UP IF THEY WANT TO, BUT IF THEY DON'T

00:51:43.630 --> 00:51:47.640
WANT TO SERVE, THEY DON'T HAVE TO.

00:51:47.640 --> 00:51:54.560
THE POINT THAT OUR LAWYERS TREID TO MAKE TO
THE SUPREME COURT WAS KEEPING WOMEN OFF THE

00:51:54.560 --> 00:52:00.960
JURY ROLLS SAYS SOMETHING ABOUT HOW THE STATE
REGARDS ITS CITIZENS.

00:52:00.960 --> 00:52:04.089
CITIZENS HAVE OBLIGATIONS AS WELL AS RIGHTS.

00:52:04.089 --> 00:52:08.959
AND ONE OBLIGATION IS TO BE PART OF THE ADMINISTRATION
OF JUSTICE.

00:52:08.959 --> 00:52:15.660
SO A LAW THAT SAYS WOMEN AREN'T ON JURIES
UNLESS THEY VOLUNTEER IS SAYING THAT WOMEN

00:52:15.660 --> 00:52:16.660
ARE EXPENDABLE.

00:52:16.660 --> 00:52:20.880
WE DON'T NEED THEM IN THIS JUSTICE SYSTEM.

00:52:20.880 --> 00:52:24.160
IF THEY WANT TO, WE'LL ALLOW THEM.

00:52:24.160 --> 00:52:26.690
THE MEN, ON THE OTHER HAND, ARE ESSENTIAL.

00:52:26.690 --> 00:52:32.249
SO WE CAN'T GIVE THEM EXEMPTIONS FROM JURY
DUTY.

00:52:32.249 --> 00:52:42.249
THAT WAS GWENDOLYN HOYT'S CASE IN 1961. THERE
WAS A SEA CHANGE IN ATTITUDE BY THE '70s.

00:52:42.249 --> 00:52:45.640
MORE AND MORE WOMEN WERE IN THE WORKFORCE.

00:52:45.640 --> 00:52:58.119
IT BECAME INCREASINGLY EASIER TO CONTROL,
A WOMAN TO CONTROL HER REPRODUCTIVE CAPACITY.

00:52:58.119 --> 00:53:01.709
PEOPLE WERE LIVING LONGER.

00:53:01.709 --> 00:53:06.140
AND THERE WAS QUITE A HIGH DEGREE OF INFLATION.

00:53:06.140 --> 00:53:10.209
SO THE TWO EARNER FAMILY BECAME THE IDEAL.

00:53:10.209 --> 00:53:19.700
IT WAS THAT CHANGE THAT HAD ALREADY OCCURRED
IN SOCIETY THAT LED THE COURT AT LAST TO CATCH

00:53:19.700 --> 00:53:22.079
UP TO THAT CHANGE.

00:53:22.079 --> 00:53:26.440
&gt;&gt; KATHLEEN SULLIVAN: AND I THINK IT'S WORTH
STOPPING TO NOTE HOW REMARKABLE IT WAS THAT

00:53:26.440 --> 00:53:31.079
YOU WON THOSE SEX DISCRIMINATION CASES IN
THE EARLY '70s, AFTER JUST A DECADE THAT THE

00:53:31.079 --> 00:53:36.509
SUPREME COURT REFUSED TO FIND IT DISCRIMINATION
TO KEEP WOMEN OFF THE JURY ROLLS.

00:53:36.509 --> 00:53:40.440
SO THAT'S A REMARKABLE CHANGE IN A SHORT AMOUNT
OF TIME DUE VERY MUCH TO ADVOCACY AS WELL

00:53:40.440 --> 00:53:42.259
AS SOCIAL EVOLUTION.

00:53:42.259 --> 00:53:49.059
BUT YOU FAMOUSLY SAID ONCE THAT THE COURT
CAN'T GET OUT TOO FAR AHEAD OF SOCIAL CONSENSUS

00:53:49.059 --> 00:53:51.410
AND POPULAR OPINION.

00:53:51.410 --> 00:53:59.619
MAYBE THE NATION NEEDED MORE TIME TO PERCOLATE
BEFORE ROE VS. WADE WAS DECIDED. HOW DO WE

00:53:59.619 --> 00:54:06.209
KNOW WHEN POPULAR OPINION AND SOCIAL CONSENSUS
HAS COME FAR ENOUGH? WHEN DO WE LOOK TO?

00:54:06.209 --> 00:54:12.709
&gt;&gt; RUTH BADER GINSBURG: IT WASN'T SO MUCH
THAT ROE WAS AHEAD OF ITS TIME.

00:54:12.709 --> 00:54:16.449
IT WAS REALLY THE WAY THAT THE COURT DECIDED.

00:54:16.449 --> 00:54:20.059
IT WAS AN UNUSUAL DECISION IN THIS RESPECT.

00:54:20.059 --> 00:54:28.019
IN ONE FELL SWOOP THE COURT MADE UNCONSTITUTIONAL
EVERY ABORTION LAW IN THE COUNTRY.

00:54:28.019 --> 00:54:33.910
EVEN THE MOST LIBERAL STATES DIDN'T SATISFY
THE STANDARDS SET IN THAT CASE.

00:54:33.910 --> 00:54:35.920
SO THE COURT HAD DONE IT ALL.

00:54:35.920 --> 00:54:46.499
AND THE PEOPLE WHO WERE ADVOCATING FOR A WOMAN'S
ABILITY TO CONTROL HER OWN DESTINY, THEY RETIRED,

00:54:46.499 --> 00:54:48.920
WHILE THE OPPOSITION MOUNTED.

00:54:48.920 --> 00:54:54.119
NOW THEY HAD INSTEAD OF HAVING TO FIGHT IN
THE TRENCHES STATE BY STATE, SOMETIMES WINNING,

00:54:54.119 --> 00:54:58.680
SOMETIMES LOSING, THEY HAD THIS ONE SINGLE
TARGET TO AIM AT.

00:54:58.680 --> 00:55:00.670
THIS DECISION.

00:55:00.670 --> 00:55:05.839
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN AN EASY THING TO DO, TO
DECLARE THE TEXAS LAW THAT WAS IN FRONT OF

00:55:05.839 --> 00:55:12.440
THE COURT UNCONSTITUTIONAL BECAUSE THE ONLY
GROUND FOR ABORTION IN TEXAS AT THE TIME WAS

00:55:12.440 --> 00:55:14.039
THE LIFE OF THE WOMAN.

00:55:14.039 --> 00:55:18.170
NOT HER HEALTH. HER HEALTH COULD BE DEVASTATED
IT DIDN'T MATTER.

00:55:18.170 --> 00:55:19.529
JUST HER LIFE.

00:55:19.529 --> 00:55:20.980
THAT WAS TOO EXTREME.

00:55:20.980 --> 00:55:26.359
THE COURT COULD HAVE SAID THAT AND PUT DOWN
ITS PEN AND THEN LET THE POLITICAL SYSTEM

00:55:26.359 --> 00:55:27.380
REACT TO THAT.

00:55:27.380 --> 00:55:32.140
&gt;&gt; KATHLEEN SULLIVAN: SO SOMETIMES THE NATURE
OF THE DECISION AND THE RATE OF CHANGE IS

00:55:32.140 --> 00:55:36.779
JUST AS IMPORTANT AS THE COUNTRY'S READINESS
FOR CHANGE.

00:55:36.779 --> 00:55:41.289
MAYBE WE COULD FAST FORWARD NOW TO THE TIME
YOU HAD ON THE BENCH.

00:55:41.289 --> 00:55:46.160
YOU HAD THE REMARKABLE PRIVILEGE OF NOT ONLY
ARGUING AS AN ADVOCATE AND WINNING SOME OF

00:55:46.160 --> 00:55:50.420
THE MOST IMPORTANT SEX DISCRIMINATION CASES
IN OUR NATION'S HISTORY.

00:55:50.420 --> 00:55:54.630
YOU THEN SITTING ON THE COURT HAD THE CHANCE
TO AUTHOR SOME OF THEM.

00:55:54.630 --> 00:55:59.449
I WONDER IF YOU COULD SHARE WITH US SOME OBSERVATIONS
ABOUT WRITING THE OPINION FOR THE COURT IN

00:55:59.449 --> 00:56:04.010
THE VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE CASE, WHICH
HELD THAT WOMEN COULDN'T BE EXCLUDED FROM

00:56:04.010 --> 00:56:10.910
A PUBLIC MILITARY INSTITUTE, NOT EVEN IF THERE
WAS ANOTHER SCHOOL FOR GIRLS NEARBY.

00:56:10.910 --> 00:56:23.809
&gt;&gt; RUTH BADER GINSBURG: PERHAPS I SHOULD START
WITH A CASE THAT WAS 20 YEARS EARLIER.

00:56:23.809 --> 00:56:29.279
IT WAS SUSAN VORCHHEIMER'S CASE AGAINST THE
PHILADELPHIA BOARD OF EDUCATION.

00:56:29.279 --> 00:56:34.930
THERE WERE TWO HIGH SCHOOLS FOR GIFTED CHILDREN
IN PHILADELPHIA.

00:56:34.930 --> 00:56:38.599
THE NAMES OF THE SCHOOLS I THINK TELL THE
STORY.

00:56:38.599 --> 00:56:39.809
ONE WAS GIRLS HIGH.

00:56:39.809 --> 00:56:43.779
AND THE OTHER WAS CENTRAL HIGH.

00:56:43.779 --> 00:56:45.489
[LAUGHTER]

00:56:45.489 --> 00:56:51.180
A YOUNG GIRL NOTICING THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN
THESE TWO SCHOOLS SAID I DON'T WANT TO GO

00:56:51.180 --> 00:56:57.359
TO THE GIRLS HIGH, I WANT TO GO TO THE CENTRAL
HIGH WHERE THEY HAVE BETTER SCIENCE AND MATH

00:56:57.359 --> 00:57:01.240
FACILITIES, A MUCH BETTER LIBRARY.

00:57:01.240 --> 00:57:09.189
OF COURSE INFINITELY BETTER SPORTS FACILITIES.

00:57:09.189 --> 00:57:17.049
SO SHE STARTED HER CASE IN THE FEDERAL DISTRICT
COURT AND SHE WON.

00:57:17.049 --> 00:57:23.549
IT WENT UP ON APPEALS, AND THE COURT OF APPEALS
REVERSED TWO TO ONE.

00:57:23.549 --> 00:57:31.420
SHE PETITIONED AND THE SUPREME COURT SPLIT
FOUR TO FOUR.

00:57:31.420 --> 00:57:39.979
THAT MEANS YOU AUTOMATICALLY AFFIRM THE DECISION
OF THE COURT ONE STEP BELOW.

00:57:39.979 --> 00:57:44.249
WRITE NO OPINION, IT HAS NO PRESIDENTIAL VALUE.

00:57:44.249 --> 00:57:53.110
THE FEDERAL COURTS WERE EVENLY DIVIDED WITH
TWO IN THE LOWER COURTS ON EACH SIDE AND THE

00:57:53.110 --> 00:57:56.809
SUPREME COURT FOUR TO FOUR.

00:57:56.809 --> 00:58:00.119
I HAD WRITTEN THE BRIEF IN THE VORCHHEIMER
CASE BUT IT WAS ARGUED BY LOCAL COUNSEL.

00:58:00.119 --> 00:58:09.520
AND WHEN THE VMI DECISION CAME OUT, MY DEAR
HUSBAND SAID TO ME WELL RUTH IT TOOK YOU 20

00:58:09.520 --> 00:58:12.859
YEARS TO WIN THE VORCHHEIMER CASE, BUT YOU
FINALLY DID IT.

00:58:12.859 --> 00:58:13.859
[APPLAUSE]

00:58:13.859 --> 00:58:17.369
BUT THE CHANGE IN THE TIME IS INTERESTING.

00:58:17.369 --> 00:58:22.180
BECAUSE THE NAME OF THE VMI CASE IS UNITED
STATES AGAINST VIRGINIA.

00:58:22.180 --> 00:58:32.779
SO IT WAS OUR GOVERNMENT URGING THAT NO PUBLIC
INSTITUTION COULD EXCLUDE ON THE BASIS OF

00:58:32.779 --> 00:58:35.650
GENDER.

00:58:35.650 --> 00:58:41.950
THE GOVERNMENT TAKING UP THE CLAIM OF THE
WOMEN WHO WANTED TO BE ADMITTED TO VMI.

00:58:41.950 --> 00:58:51.339
SOME PEOPLE SAID TO ME ABOUT THE VMI CASE,
WELL, WHY WOULD WOMEN WANT TO GO TO THAT SCHOOL?

00:58:51.339 --> 00:58:55.630
WELL, I WOULDN'T WANT TO.

00:58:55.630 --> 00:58:59.319
PERHAPS, YOU, A MAN WOULD NOT WANT TO EITHER.

00:58:59.319 --> 00:59:04.930
BUT THERE ARE SOME WOMEN WHO SEE THAT AS THE
RIGHT PLACE FOR THEM.

00:59:04.930 --> 00:59:09.289
AND WHO ARE FULLY EQUIPPED TO SURVIVE THE
RIGOROUS REGIME.

00:59:09.289 --> 00:59:16.219
WHY SHOULD THEY BE HELD BACK SIMPLY BECAUSE
THEY ARE WOMEN?

00:59:16.219 --> 00:59:26.469
AND SO THE VMI CASE WAS VERY SATISFYING IN
MANY WAYS.

00:59:26.469 --> 00:59:31.349
FOR ONE THING, THE VMI FACULTY WAS VERY MUCH
IN FAVOR OF THE ADMISSION OF WOMEN.

00:59:31.349 --> 00:59:34.079
THE REASON SHOULD BE OBVIOUS.

00:59:34.079 --> 00:59:44.450
IF THEY COULD INCLUDE WOMEN IN THEIR APPLICANT
POOL, THEY WOULD UPGRADE THE QUALITY OF THEIR

00:59:44.450 --> 00:59:45.969
STUDENTS.

00:59:45.969 --> 00:59:47.499
[APPLAUSE]

00:59:47.499 --> 00:59:55.789
&gt;&gt; KATHLEEN SULLIVAN: WELL THAT WAS A REMARKABLE
DECISION AND ONE OF MANY IMPORTANT ONES YOU

00:59:55.789 --> 00:59:56.789
WROTE ON THE COURT.

00:59:56.789 --> 00:59:58.259
I WISH WE HAD MORE TIME TO TALK ABOUT ALL
OF THEM.

00:59:58.259 --> 01:00:03.400
BUT MAYBE WE COULD TALK A BIT MORE BROADLY
ABOUT THE COURT ITSELF AND ABOUT THE COLLEGIALLY

01:00:03.400 --> 01:00:09.579
WE SAW ON THAT MAGNIFICENT DISPLAY WE SAW
TODAY IN JUSTICE SOUTER'S REMARKS ABOUT YOU

01:00:09.579 --> 01:00:14.609
AND YOUR REMARKS IN DUET WITH HIM ABOUT HOW
MUCH YOU ENJOYED BEING HIS COLLEAGUE.

01:00:14.609 --> 01:00:18.069
BUT THE TWO OF YOU DID AGREE QUITE A BIT.

01:00:18.069 --> 01:00:23.440
BUT WE UNDERSTAND THAT THERE'S AN OPERA CALLED
SCALIA/GINSBURG THAT ADDRESSES SOME OF THE

01:00:23.440 --> 01:00:26.199
DIFFERENCES BETWEEN YOU AND JUSTICE SCALIA.

01:00:26.199 --> 01:00:28.239
AND YET YOU'RE GREAT FRIENDS.

01:00:28.239 --> 01:00:32.630
AND YOU GO TO THE OPERA TOGETHER AND YOU HAVE
COLLEGIATELY THAT I THINK YOU'VE DESCRIBED

01:00:32.630 --> 01:00:39.209
AS BEING TRUE OF ALL THE MEMBER OF THE COURT.
SO HOW CAN IT BE THAT AS THE CLOSING DUET

01:00:39.209 --> 01:00:45.359
OF SCALIA/GINSBURG GOES YOU CAN BE ON THE
COURT WITH PEOPLE WHO SAY TO EACH OTHER, AS

01:00:45.359 --> 01:00:47.749
YOU AND SAID TO SING TO EACH OTHER.

01:00:47.749 --> 01:00:50.569
WE ARE DIFFERENT, WE ARE ONE.

01:00:50.569 --> 01:00:51.710
HOW DOES THAT WORK?

01:00:51.710 --> 01:00:58.619
&gt;&gt; RUTH BADER GINSBURG: I WOULD LIKE TO EXPLAIN
FIRST WHY THIS OPERA IS CALLED SCALIA/GINSBURG,

01:00:58.619 --> 01:01:04.630
BECAUSE SOME OF MY FEMINIST COLLEAGUES HAVE
SAID YOU COME FIRST ALPHABETICALLY! IT SHOULD

01:01:04.630 --> 01:01:15.349
BE GINSBERG/SCALIA. I EXPLAIN THAT IN THE
UNITED STATES SUPREME COURT SENIORITY IS VERY

01:01:15.349 --> 01:01:16.479
IMPORTANT.

01:01:16.479 --> 01:01:27.079
SCALIA WAS APPOINTED IN THE '80s. SO HE'S
A FEW STEPS AHEAD OF GINSBURG.

01:01:27.079 --> 01:01:30.599
BY SENIORITY, IT'S SCALIA, GINSBURG.

01:01:30.599 --> 01:01:41.279
THE CLOSING ARIA, WHAT IT PORTRAYS IS WE HAVE
DIFFERENT VIEWS ON HOW OUR CONSTITUTION SHOULD

01:01:41.279 --> 01:01:43.189
BE INTERPRETED.

01:01:43.189 --> 01:01:53.339
BUT WE REVERE THE COURT AND WE WANT TO MAKE
SURE THAT WE DON'T DO ANY DAMAGE TO IT.

01:01:53.339 --> 01:02:01.920
SO DIFFERENT IN OUR VIEWS, BUT ONE IN OUR
REVERENCE FOR THE FEDERAL JUDICIAL SYSTEM.

01:02:01.920 --> 01:02:06.859
&gt;&gt; KATHLEEN SULLIVAN: DO YOU WANT TO TELL
PEOPLE HOW THE OPERA OPENS?

01:02:06.859 --> 01:02:08.069
WHAT THE DIFFERENCES ARE?

01:02:08.069 --> 01:02:13.819
&gt;&gt; RUTH BADER GINSBURG: WELL THE OPERA IS
BORROWED FROM MANY LONG DEAD COMPOSERS.

01:02:13.819 --> 01:02:16.969
LONG DEAD BECAUSE THERE'S NO COPYRIGHT PROBLEMS.

01:02:16.969 --> 01:02:24.380
SO SCALIA'S OPENING ARIA IS HANDELLIAN. IT'S
A RAGE ARIA.

01:02:24.380 --> 01:02:28.839
IT GOES THIS WAY.

01:02:28.839 --> 01:02:30.299
THE JUSTICES ARE BLIND.

01:02:30.299 --> 01:02:34.180
HOW CAN THEY POSSIBLY SPOUT THIS.

01:02:34.180 --> 01:02:41.209
THE CONSTITUTION SAID ABSOLUTELY NOTHING ABOUT
THIS.

01:02:41.209 --> 01:02:55.739
AND IF YOU WOULD LIKE TO KNOW ABOUT MY ANSWERING
ARIA, IT IS YOU ARE SEARCHING FOR BRIGHT LINE

01:02:55.739 --> 01:03:04.559
SOLUTIONS TO PROBLEMS THAT DON'T HAVE EASY
ANSWERS BUT THE GREAT THING ABOUT OUR CONSTITUTION

01:03:04.559 --> 01:03:06.819
IT CAN EVOLVE!

01:03:06.819 --> 01:03:07.859
[APPLAUSE]

01:03:07.859 --> 01:03:25.730
AND THEN ONE OF THE MOST IMPORTANT SCENES,
AND I'M EAGER TO SEE THIS PERFORMED, IS JUSTICE

01:03:25.730 --> 01:03:32.039
SCALIA HAS BEEN LOCKED UP IN A DARK ROOM BEING
PUNISHED FOR EXCESSIVE DISSENTING.

01:03:32.039 --> 01:03:33.039
[LAUGHTER]

01:03:33.039 --> 01:03:46.359
AND I COME TO HIS RESCUE ENTERING THROUGH
A GLASS CEILING.

01:03:46.359 --> 01:03:48.160
[LAUGHTER]

01:03:48.160 --> 01:03:49.970
[APPLAUSE]

01:03:49.970 --> 01:03:58.069
&gt;&gt; KATHLEEN SULLIVAN: WELL I THINK THIS IS
A FITTING NOTE ON WHICH TO END OUR CONVERSATION.

01:03:58.069 --> 01:04:03.069
BECAUSE A REALLY IMPORTANT NEXT STEP NEEDS
TO OCCUR, THE AWARDING OF THE RADCLIFFE MEDAL.

01:04:03.069 --> 01:04:07.450
THERE ISN'T A GLASS CEILING YOU HAVEN'T BROKEN.

01:04:07.450 --> 01:04:14.049
AS BRILLIANT PROFESSOR, AS ORIGINATOR OF AN
ENTIRE LINE OF SCHOLARSHIP, ON GENDER DISCRIMINATION,

01:04:14.049 --> 01:04:15.839
AS BRILLIANT LAWYER.

01:04:15.839 --> 01:04:17.209
ALL WITHOUT ROLE MODELS.

01:04:17.209 --> 01:04:22.700
THERE WEREN'T WOMEN FEDERAL JUDGES BEFORE
1949. AND THEN OF COURSE AS THE SECOND WOMAN

01:04:22.700 --> 01:04:29.119
JUSTICE ON THE SUPREME COURT AND A GREAT JUSTICE,
THANK YOU FOR THE INSPIRATION YOU HAVE GIVEN

01:04:29.119 --> 01:04:38.289
TO ALL OF US WHO ARE PRIVILEGED TO HAVE BENEFITED
FROM THE PATHWAYS YOU HAVE FORGED IN THE LAW.

01:04:38.289 --> 01:04:42.249
AND LET ME JUST CLOSE BY ASKING YOU TO SAY
ONE LAST THING ABOUT WHAT YOU WOULD SAY TO

01:04:42.249 --> 01:04:47.890
THE YOUNG WOMEN OF TODAY, IF SO MUCH COULD
CHANGE IN YOUR CAREER AND THROUGH YOUR CAREER,

01:04:47.890 --> 01:04:51.569
WHAT DO YOU THINK IS THE MOST INSPIRATIONAL
MESSAGE YOU HAVE FOR THEM?

01:04:51.569 --> 01:05:00.420
&gt;&gt; RUTH BADER GINSBURG: YOUNG WOMEN TODAY
HAVE THIS GREAT ADVANTAGE IS THAT THERE ARE

01:05:00.420 --> 01:05:04.430
NO DOORS, NO MORE CLOSED DOORS.

01:05:04.430 --> 01:05:07.719
THAT WAS BASICALLY WHAT THE '70s WERE ABOUT.

01:05:07.719 --> 01:05:10.749
OPENING DOORS THAT HAD BEEN CLOSED TO WOMEN.

01:05:10.749 --> 01:05:23.679
SO MY ADVICE, WHAT IS MY ADVICE, IS FIGHT
FOR THE THINGS THAT YOU CARE ABOUT.

01:05:23.679 --> 01:05:34.839
BUT DO IT IN A WAY THAT WILL LEAD OTHERS TO
JOIN YOU.

01:05:34.839 --> 01:05:37.150
THAT IS, ONE VITAL ASSET

01:05:37.150 --> 01:05:43.869
IS A SENSE OF HUMOR.

01:05:43.869 --> 01:05:50.449
SO I DON'T KNOW HOW MANY PUTDOWNS I HAVE TURNED
AWAY THAT WAY.

01:05:50.449 --> 01:05:59.549
THE REMARK WAS MADE ABOUT THEN JUSTICE REHNQUIST
SAYING AT THE END OF THE MISSOURI JURY CASE.

01:05:59.549 --> 01:06:04.979
SO MRS. GINSBERG YOU WON'T SETTLE FOR SUSAN
B. ANTHONY'S FACE ON THE NEW DOLLAR?

01:06:04.979 --> 01:06:13.400
A PERFECT ANSWER WHICH I DIDN'T THINK OF ON
THE SPOT WOULD HAVE BEEN NO, JUSTICE REHNQUIST,

01:06:13.400 --> 01:06:14.530
TOKENS WON'T DO.

01:06:14.530 --> 01:06:15.530
[APPLAUSE]

01:06:15.530 --> 01:06:16.530
&gt;&gt; KATHLEEN SULLIVAN: LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
THANK YOU TO JUSTICE GINSBURG.

01:06:16.530 --> 01:06:20.569
I'LL TURN IT BACK OVER TO DEAN COHEN.

01:06:20.569 --> 01:06:37.359
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

01:06:37.359 --> 01:06:48.559
&gt;&gt; THANK YOU.

01:06:48.559 --> 01:06:56.819
I WILL SPEAK I THINK FOR EVERYONE IN THIS
ROOM, IN THIS TENT, TO THANK YOU KATHLEEN

01:06:56.819 --> 01:07:04.460
SULLIVAN FOR BEING SUCH A SPECTACULAR TEACHER
AS JUSTICE SOUTER TOLD US YOU ARE.

01:07:04.460 --> 01:07:08.650
AND FOR BEING PART OF ANOTHER RADCLIFFE DAY,
YOU WERE ON THE PANEL WHEN WE GAVE THE MEDAL

01:07:08.650 --> 01:07:16.630
TO MARGIE MARSHALL, AND FOR SHARING YOUR INTELLIGENCE,
